This repository contains the Todos app from the SproutCore "Getting Started With HTML-Based Apps" Guide at 
http://guides.sproutcore.com/html_based.html

It includes a progressive commit history that roughly corresponds to the steps of the guide.

To install or get started,

(0) if you don't have RVM, get it! http://rvm.beginrescueend.com/

(1) clone this repo into "todos": $ git clone git://github.com/concord-consortium/SC-HTML-Guide-Todos.git todos

(2) $ cd todos

(3) RVM will ask you to trust the .rvmrc file. Trust it. It may also tell you to install ruby-1.9.2. In that case, type:

    $ rvm install 1.9.2

(4) make sure you are using the specified gemset:

    $ rvm current

    ...should respond with "ruby-1.9.2-p180@todos" or the like
    
(5) $ bundle install

(6) $ sc-server -v

(7) $ open http://localhost:4020/todos